        <updateDate>2006-11-28T17:35:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[Restoring Investor Confidence Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to revise rules concerning capital gain for taxpayers other than corporations to establish a new general rule which provides that if for any taxable year a taxpayer other than a corporation has a capital gain, 55 percent of such gain shall be a deduction from gross income.<p>Excludes from individual gross income 55 percent of dividends received from a domestic corporation.]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Restoring Investor Confidence Act of 2003</title>
